<h1>How Do I Prepare<br />for Education Week?</h1>
<p>At Education Week we will use the BYU Idaho Learning Model, which consists of a three-part approach: <em>prepare, teach one another,</em> and <em>ponder and prove.</em> Education Week will follow this pattern in the following ways:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Prepare (before Education Week):</strong> Materials to prepare for each class can be found by clicking on a class you are interested in attending. The classes offered&nbsp;will be found on the Education Week website.</li>
<li><strong>Teach One Another (during Education Week):</strong> You can get the most out of Education Week by participating in both learning from and teaching others. Having prepared beforehand, you may be prepared with personal experiences and/or insights that, if you feel prompted to share them, may contribute to the learning of those attending the class with you.</li>
<li><strong>Ponder and Prove (after Education Week):</strong> Materials to discuss topics presented during education week can also be found on the Education Week website. These materials can be utilized during a Family Home Evening, Family Council, or any other appropriate setting.</li>
</ul>
<p>Further information on the Learning Model can be found by visiting the <a class="extLink" href="http://www2.byui.edu/LearningModel/src/default.htm" title="BYUI_Learning_Model_ED_WEEK">Learning Model website </a>.</p>
